  "prompt": "Where are Samsung phones made?",
  "response": "Samsung phones are primarily manufactured in several countries around the world, with a significant portion of production taking place in **Vietnam**. Vietnam is home to Samsung's largest smartphone production facilities, which produce a major share of the company's global output.\n\nOther countries where Samsung phones are assembled include:\n\n1. **South Korea**: Some high-end models and prototypes are produced in Samsung's home country.\n2. **India**: Samsung has a large manufacturing plant in Noida, which serves both the domestic market and exports to other regions.\n3. **China**: Certain models are also produced in China, though production has been scaled back in recent years due to rising costs and geopolitical factors.\n4. **Brazil**: Samsung has a manufacturing facility in Brazil to cater to the Latin American market.\n5. **Indonesia**: The company also has a production plant in Indonesia to meet regional demand.\n\nThis global manufacturing strategy allows Samsung to optimize costs, reduce logistical challenges, and cater to specific market needs.",
